dt.t: {ldquo}It's a heritage. My mother was a witch and her mother was a witch. My specialty is (prophetic) dreaming. We believe {wi}elementals{/wi} do exist,{rdquo} said Lady L …
All objects consist of smaller objects. … Lamps, bicycles, and houses are compound objects made of constituent parts, or {wi}elementals{/wi}.

These two epistemologies exist in distinct dimensions: science struggles to discover the {wi}elementals{/wi} of our material existence through empiricism, and theology strives to describe the universality of our … existence through faith.

shortdef: an elementary part or principle —usually plural
